# Git push on Windows (agents)

**reactwoo-flow `origin` must be SSH:** `git@github.com:reactwoo/reactwoo-flow.git` (not HTTPS).

Push (standalone — never chain with commit/tag):

```bash
GIT_SSH_COMMAND="ssh -o BatchMode=yes -o ConnectTimeout=15" git push origin main
```

Or: `bash scripts/push-main.sh` (optional tag arg for release push).

## Stop — do not waste tokens retrying

- Hung push (no output ~30s) → stop; report repo + `git remote get-url origin`.
- Exit **139** or **-1073741819** → one retry in new shell, then stop.
- One repo at a time when pushing multiple plugins.

See `reactwoo-geocore/docs/git-push-windows.md` and `.cursor/rules/release.mdc`.
